---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Accessibility | FashionCulture">
    <main>
        <section class="accessibility-section">
            <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>

            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    FashionCulture is committed to ensuring that our website is accessible to everyone, including individuals with disabilities. We strive to provide a seamless shopping experience for all users and continuously work to enhance the accessibility and usability of our website.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
                <p>
                    We are dedicated to meeting the needs of all our customers, and we actively work to adhere to the best practices and standards set by the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG). Our goal is to make our website accessible to the widest possible audience, regardless of technology or ability.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
                <p>
                    Our website includes a variety of features designed to improve accessibility for users with disabilities, including:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> Our website is designed to be navigable using a keyboard, allowing users to move through content and interact with elements without the need for a mouse.</li>
                    <li><strong>Text Alternatives:</strong> We provide text alternatives for non-text content, such as images, to ensure that users with visual impairments can access the information they need.</li>
                    <li><strong>Adjustable Text Size:</strong> Users can adjust the text size on our website to improve readability according to their preferences.</li>
                    <li><strong>Color Contrast:</strong> We ensure that there is sufficient color contrast between text and background elements to make content more readable for users with visual impairments.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Ongoing Efforts</h2>
                <p>
                    Accessibility is an ongoing process, and we are continually seeking out new solutions that will bring all areas of our website to the same level of accessibility. We regularly review our website to identify and correct any accessibility issues.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Feedback and Assistance</h2>
                <p>
                    We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of the FashionCulture website. If you encounter any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please let us know. You can contact us at <a href="mailto:support@fashionculture.com">support@fashionculture.com</a>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you need assistance with any part of our website or have difficulty accessing any content, our customer support team is here to help. Please reach out to us, and we will work with you to provide the information or service you need in an accessible format.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Third-Party Content</h2>
                <p>
                    While we strive to ensure that all content on our website is accessible, there may be some third-party content or applications that are not fully compliant with accessibility standards. We are committed to working with these third parties to improve accessibility wherever possible.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Updates to This Accessibility Statement</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update our Accessibility Statement from time to time to reflect improvements or changes in our practices. We encourage you to review this page periodically to stay informed about our accessibility efforts.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <style>
        main {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 20px;
            font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        .accessibility-section {
            max-width: 800px;
            width: 100%;
            background-color: white;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5em;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            color: #444;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.8em;
            margin-top: 30px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            color: #555;
        }

        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .content-block {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        strong {
            color: #000;
        }

        a {
            color: #007bff;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
    </style>
</Layout>
